assets.name: assets/atcXklEolS6
assets.description:
A collage of imagery from Jay Tripper's House of VR Artist Residency.

The Google Tilt Brush painting is an homage to the great artist Alan Aldridge who was famous for having illustrated lyrics for The Beatles and other bands from the 1960s and 1970s. This will be an expanding universe of Beatles lyrics and influences and hidden Easter eggs for people to one day explore and enjoy.

My future goal is to create 3D environments for bands and Djs and other artists to share with their fans and followers to literally add another dimension to their music. Imagine being able to strap on a set of goggles and stepping into surreal and psychedelic environments created to enhance and visualize the songs and lyrics that swallow you whole. Reach out if you are interested in having 3D environments made for your work, or to book me for a LIVE VR PAINTING PERFORMANCE at an event or gathering.

Special thanks to the lovely people at House of VR for sponsoring me and allowing me to learn this beautiful new form of expression. The residency also culminated in a live VR performance at Yonge and Dundas Square in the heart of downtown Toronto on epic big screens visible from all around the square. Stay tuned for video footage and more!

Much love from Jay Tripper
It's Worth the Trip to www.JayTripper.com

assets.name: assets/blUt19iMscG
assets.description:
I made this for my boss, roll model, and friend. There are talking phish, and a hidden message in the flower. This is a special one of a kind just for her thing or I would gladly allow remixing. I do hope others find beauty in it as well. The creative brain and process is one of the greatest things we were given in life. It can help in problem solving, Substance use disorder, and mental health conditions. I created this piece in grate depression over grieving my mother as well as being isolated and sick ( its not covid-19) if you are in the future you might have to look that one up, ha. My mother may be gone but creating this made my realize who I do have in my like and just how special that is. 
update: remix away

assets.name: assets/eikMp9aT_Uc
assets.description:
Deep and synthetic sounds are seeping through the walls of this floating UFO, giving the art revelers, a hint of whats hidden on the inner side. But within these organic shapes, a different kind of experience awaits: a club for all those mutants living on the Inter-net-space where diversity reigns and the limits of consciousness are constantly being pushed.

To celebrate integration, the club admits every form of posthuman life. The code is to follow its own personal style and be open to meeting a variety of humanoids, avatars, aliens and any kind of digital lifeform who are welcome to party in this cyber happening.
This pavilion proposes an immersive and multisensory experience on the craziest VR dancefloor. An opportunity to dance among living artworks and enjoy hot music.
Come and join the party!
http://www.mutantclub.net/
